I’ve been working on autos using pathplanner, and for some reason when I run an auto that should just move the robot forward about a foot forwards, none of the wheels move in the same direction. The right two wheels move fairly close to straight, however the left two are at almost a 90 degree angle from the right set.
Here’s a link to the github repo I’ve been working on
If anyone has any idea what could be causing this, it would be greatly appreciated.
